cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.IT

The paper discusses optimization methods for over-parameterized systems of non-linear equations, which is a common problem in deep learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the Polyak-Lojasiewicz (PL) condition, which is a condition related to optimization, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Additionally, the paper mentions the application of these ideas to training shallow and deep neural networks, which could place it in cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the tangent kernel associated with these systems, which could also place it in cs.IT (Information Theory).
